{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-b1935ae5cd74493a", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# QuarkAudio Technical Report\narXiv: 2512.20151\nAuthors: Chengwei Liu, Haoyin Yan, Shaofei Xue, Xiaotao Liang, Xiaofu Chen, Bin Gong, Zheng Xue, Gang Song\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present H-Codec, a unified discrete audio tokenizer that integrates self-supervised learning representations into the tokenization process via dual-stream (acoustic and semantic) quantization, achieving remarkable audio reconstruction quality at a low frame rate.\n  2. We introduce advanced H-Codec variants, including H-Codec-1.5 with a dynamic frame-rate mechanism for adaptive temporal resolution and H-Codec-2.0 extending the sampling rate to 48 kHz for higher fidelity.\n  3. We propose QuarkAudio, a unified decoder-only autoregressive language model framework that uses task-specific conditional information and special task tokens to distinguish and unify multiple audio processing and generation tasks within a single set of shared weights.\n  4. We extend unified audio generation to universal free-form audio editing guided by natural language instructions, covering both speech semantic editing and audio event editing.\n  5. We demonstrate that QuarkAudio achieves competitive or comparable high-fidelity generation performance against state-of-the-art task-specific or multi-task systems across speech restoration, target speaker extraction, speech separation, voice conversion, and language-queried audio source separation tasks.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/功能-语音编辑, TTS/功能-多任务统一, 压缩, 压缩/量化-RVQ, 压缩/语义声学-语义, 压缩/语义声学-声学\n---\n# Metis: A Foundation Speech Generation Model with Masked Generative Pre-training\narXiv: 2502.03128\nAuthors: Yuancheng Wang, Jiachen Zheng, Junan Zhang, Xueyao Zhang, Huan Liao, Zhizheng Wu\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Metis performs masked generative pre-training on SSL tokens using large-scale unlabeled speech data without any task-specific condition.\n  2. Metis efficiently adapts to various speech generation tasks through fine-tuning with task-specific conditions, achieving state-of-the-art results with limited data and trainable parameters.\n  3. Metis supports multimodal conditional inputs during fine-tuning, enabling diverse speech generation tasks and novel applications like text-guided target speaker extraction through multi-task combinations.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/功能-多任务统一, TTS/控制-参考语音", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "79eb4d26-dfee-4e59-b51a-c78a1592b002", "uuid": "7e1ec1b8-684d-468f-95c5-c2e6fb5ab961", "timestamp": "2026-07-14T07:49:05.818Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# QuarkAudio Technical Report\narXiv: 2512.20151\nAuthors: Chengwei Liu, Haoyin Yan, Shaofei Xue, Xiaotao Liang, Xiaofu Chen, Bin Gong, Zheng Xue, Gang Song\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present H-Codec, a unified discrete audio tokenizer that integrates self-supervised learning representations into the tokenization process via dual-stream (acoustic and semantic) quantization, achieving remarkable audio reconstruction quality at a low frame rate.\n  2. We introduce advanced H-Codec variants, including H-Codec-1.5 with a dynamic frame-rate mechanism for adaptive temporal resolution and H-Codec-2.0 extending the sampling rate to 48 kHz for higher fidelity.\n  3. We propose QuarkAudio, a unified decoder-only autoregressive language model framework that uses task-specific conditional information and special task tokens to distinguish and unify multiple audio processing and generation tasks within a single set of shared weights.\n  4. We extend unified audio generation to universal free-form audio editing guided by natural language instructions, covering both speech semantic editing and audio event editing.\n  5. We demonstrate that QuarkAudio achieves competitive or comparable high-fidelity generation performance against state-of-the-art task-specific or multi-task systems across speech restoration, target speaker extraction, speech separation, voice conversion, and language-queried audio source separation tasks.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/功能-语音编辑, TTS/功能-多任务统一, 压缩, 压缩/量化-RVQ, 压缩/语义声学-语义, 压缩/语义声学-声学\n---\n# Metis: A Foundation Speech Generation Model with Masked Generative Pre-training\narXiv: 2502.03128\nAuthors: Yuancheng Wang, Jiachen Zheng, Junan Zhang, Xueyao Zhang, Huan Liao, Zhizheng Wu\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Metis performs masked generative pre-training on SSL tokens using large-scale unlabeled speech data without any task-specific condition.\n  2. Metis efficiently adapts to various speech generation tasks through fine-tuning with task-specific conditions, achieving state-of-the-art results with limited data and trainable parameters.\n  3. Metis supports multimodal conditional inputs during fine-tuning, enabling diverse speech generation tasks and novel applications like text-guided target speaker extraction through multi-task combinations.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/功能-多任务统一, TTS/控制-参考语音", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
